message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Network Performance Measurement Experiment with Client, Server, and Proxy Components
abstract: This dataset documents a network performance measurement experiment involving
  client, server, and proxy components across multiple nodes. The methodology involved
  configuring network interfaces and queuing disciplines to simulate controlled network
  conditions, followed by the execution of client, server, and proxy applications
  under varying configurations. Energy consumption and packet data were captured during
  these runs, enabling evaluation of network behavior and application performance
  under different scenarios. Per-run logs and configuration contexts are included
  for reproducibility.
